Package net.philsprojects.task

Interface Summary
TaskEventHandler An event handler that can process any type of task.
TaskListener<R> A listener notified on the events of task.
 

Class Summary
Task<R> A single action that can be executed synchronously or asynchronously.
TaskCollection A collection of tasks when executed will return a list of results.
TaskFork<R> A clone of a task used for forking.
TaskGroup A collection of tasks that must start at the exact same time (execute concurrently).
TaskList A collection of tasks that must be executed in order, one after another.
TaskListenerAdapter<R> An adapter which implements all TaskListener methods.
TaskService A service which can process any type of task.
TaskServiceFactory A factory that creates TaskServers.
TaskServicePool A pool of TaskServices.
TaskSet A collection of tasks that do not have a particular execution order.
